    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <seg type="supplemental">To the Chairman &amp; Committee | of the Down School.</seg>
                    <salute>Gentlemen</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>At the next election I beg permission to resign my seat on the school-board, as the state of my health prevents my attendance; &amp; I am unwilling to take the place of a more useful man in this important duty<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Gentlemen | Your obedient servant | Ch. R. Darwin <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Nov. 16<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1874.—</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">In December 1873, ill health had prevented CD from attending the board to argue in person for the use of the schoolroom as a winter reading room for the villagers of Down (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 21, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9185.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Down School Board, 19 December 1873</ref>).</note>
        </div>        
            
